verses.roman:
'āji haite ei mora ājñā pālibā
choṭa haridāse ihāṅ āsite nā dibā'

synonyms: āji haite—from today; ei—this; mora—My; ājñā—order; pālibā—you should carry out; choṭa haridāse—Choṭa Haridāsa; ihāṅ—here; āsite—to come; nā dibā—do not allow.
translation: " From this day forward, do not allow Choṭa Haridāsa to come here."
